OL,3,CFlexible working laws could reduce
OL,4,Cregional inequality, Business
OL,5,CSecretary says
OL,7,FThe Government plans to ban the use of
OL,8,Fzero-hours contracts, make flexible
OL,9,Fworking the default, and end policies
OL,10,Fof fire and re-hire, as part of its
OL,11,FEmployment Rights Bill, which was
OL,12,Funveiled in July's King's Speech.
OL,14,FThe Bill will also remove restrictions
OL,15,Fon trade unions and give workers day
OL,16,Fone rights, such as protection from
OL,17,Funfair dismissal.
OL,19,FSpeaking to The Times, Mr Reynolds
OL,20,Fargued that flexible working
OL,21,Fcontributes to productivity.
